# -*- mode: org -*-
#+TITLE: common-library integration: status after the 2026-06 common fixes
#+DATE: 2026-06-20

* DONE [#C] common integration: verified link-compatible; no signature drift  :common:integration:
  RESOLUTION (2026-06-20). Final whole-tree build (make PREFIX=/usr/local depend
  all) against the freshly-installed common in /usr/local/lib: exit 0, zero
  errors and zero undefined references. 58 executables build; the common static
  libraries (libbclib.a, libbenlib.a, libbplib.a, and bolib/bprib/bpcombi/bjlib
  where used) link cleanly. The 2026-06 common fixes were behaviour/memory fixes,
  not signature changes, so the tools needed no API updates -- confirmed.
  DECISION on the optional BenConvertString migration: NOT done. encoding.c's own
  ConvertEncoding is correct (indexes Conversion[] with 0..255 fgetc values, so
  it was never exposed to the old signed-char bug), works, and is validated;
  migrating it would add churn/risk for no functional gain. Left as-is.
  The CARD32<->INT32 -Wconversion cleanup is a tools-side nicety noted in
  [[dosname]]; it does not affect the current build (no -Wsign-conversion).
  Context: the *common* libraries (bclib, benlib, bjlib, bolib, bplib, bprib,
  bpcombi) were reviewed and fixed in 2026-06 and reinstalled under
  =/usr/local/lib=. The concern was that tools linking them might need updates.
  This issue records the verification.

** Findings

*** [info] The whole tree links against the freshly-installed common libs
The tree was rebuilt against =/usr/local/lib/{bclib,benlib,bjlib,bolib,bplib,
bprib,bpcombi}=. There were *no* undefined-reference / signature-mismatch link
errors attributable to common: the common fixes were behaviour/memory fixes, not
API/signature changes, so the tools remain source- and link-compatible. All
build failures found are local to the tools (see the per-module issues).

*** [info] Which tools depend on common
- ascii-utilities -> benlib, bclib (encoding tables, approximations, BcRandom,
  BcTypes/FMT_* macros). API use verified correct against the installed headers.
- encoding -> benlib, bclib, bjlib. Uses =BenEncodingTableNamed/Names=,
  =BenApproximationTableNamed/Names=, =BenBuildConversionTable= correctly. The
  module Makefile already carries the bjlib -I/-l paths.
- dosname -> bplib, bclib (BpString/BpList/BpDict/BpArray). API use verified
  consistent with the installed headers.
- cookie, primes -> bclib (BcTypes / helpers).
- formats -> its own binhexlib plus bplib/bclib/bolib.

*** [low] encoding rolls its own conversion instead of BenConvertString
encoding.c does not call =BenConvertString= (the function that was just fixed for
signed-char indexing and a non-advancing loop); it implements its own
=ConvertEncoding= over =Conversion[c]=, indexing with 0..255 =fgetc= values, so it
is neither exposed to the old bug nor benefiting from the fix. Optional: migrate
to =BenConvertString= now that it is correct, to share one code path. Not urgent.

*** [low] tools assume common's unsigned length/index convention
bplib/bjlib use *unsigned* lengths/indices; the tools mostly mirror this, but the
=CARD32=<->=INT32= mixing flagged in [[dosname]] will trip =-Wconversion= if that
warning is kept. This is a tools-side cleanup, not a common change.

** Health
Integration is sound: no action required for the tools to keep working with the
new common. The only optional follow-up is consolidating encoding.c onto the
fixed =BenConvertString=.
